    "type": "Claim",
    "name": "CFD model reliably identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under CPB conditions",
    "description": "The CFD model, employing the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis correlation with SST k-omega turbulence closure, is capable of rank-ordering hemolysis across the five specified flow-speed operating points and correctly identifying the worst-case condition. The claim is scoped to the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at Model Risk Level 2, with acceptance defined by relative hemolysis index RH < 1 against the predicate device benchmark. Extensive validation results and mesh convergence studies support the overall credibility package; the model's predictive adequacy for this specific decision context has been reviewed and accepted by the assessment team.",
    "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump, CPB operating envelope, five flow-speed combinations, MRL 2",
    "purpose": "Regulatory submission support for Class II 510(k) clearance — worst-case hemolysis identification"
  },
